text: Malyye Kizeli () is a rural locality (a village) in Klenovskoye Selsoviet, Bolshesosnovsky District, Perm Krai, Russia. The population was 80 as of 2010. There are 2 streets. == Geography == It is located 7 km west from Klenovka. == References == Category:Rural localities in Bolshesosnovsky District
title: Malyye Kizeli
